🚀 Quick Deployment Guide - Vercel
Prerequisites
	∙	GitHub account
	∙	Vercel account (free tier is fine)
	∙	Your code ready to push
Step-by-Step Deployment
1️⃣ Push to GitHub
2️⃣ Deploy on Vercel
Option A: Vercel Dashboard (Recommended for First Time)
	1.	Go to https://vercel.com
	2.	Click “Sign Up” or “Login” (use GitHub account)
	3.	Click “Add New Project”
	4.	Click “Import Git Repository”
	5.	Select your alpaca-crypto-trader repository
	6.	Vercel auto-detects settings:
	∙	Framework Preset: Vite
	∙	Build Command: npm run build
	∙	Output Directory: dist
	7.	Click “Deploy”
	8.	Wait 1-2 minutes ⏳
	9.	Done! ✅ Your app is live!
Your app URL will be something like:
https://alpaca-crypto-trader.vercel.app
Option B: Vercel CLI (For Advanced Users)
3️⃣ Configure Your App
	1.	Open your deployed app URL
	2.	Go to Settings page
	3.	Enter your Alpaca API keys:
	∙	Paper Trading API Key
	∙	Paper Trading Secret Key
	∙	(Optional) Live Trading keys
	4.	Save keys
	5.	Start trading! 🎉
🔄 Updating Your App
After making changes to your code:
Vercel will automatically deploy your updates! 🚀
🎨 Custom Domain (Optional)
	1.	In Vercel dashboard, go to your project
	2.	Click “Settings” → “Domains”
	3.	Add your custom domain (e.g., mytrader.com)
	4.	Follow DNS configuration instructions
	5.	Done! Your app now runs on your domain
